name: Dalvin Cook
summary: The Dallas Cowboys have reportedly signed four-time Pro Bowl running back Dalvin Cook to a one-year contract. Cook, who was released by the Minnesota Vikings in March, visited with the Cowboys on Monday before agreeing to the deal. The move comes as the Cowboys look to bolster their backfield depth behind star running back Ezekiel Elliott. Cook, a former Florida State standout, has rushed for over 5,000 yards and 44 touchdowns in his six-year NFL career. He joins a Cowboys backfield that also includes Tony Pollard and Rico Dowdle.

name: Black Ops 6
summary: The upcoming Call of Duty: Black Ops 6 is set to deliver an exciting blend of nostalgia and innovation in its Zombies mode, according to Digital Trends. The game's multiplayer mode is also receiving significant attention, with Gaming Trend previewing its potential to reach the top spot in the genre. TechRadar provides an overview of all known details about Black Ops 6, including its release date and beta availability. The Arizona Republic confirms that the beta will go live on August 30th. PlayStation offers full details on the beta, while Variety reports on the recent Call of Duty Next 2024 event in DC, highlighting a fan wedding and the introduction of a "Black Ops 6 Monster." IGN reveals the PC requirements for the game, and Blizzard News shares insights into Black Ops 6's multiplayer. Additionally, GAMINGbible notes the influence of Forza on Black Ops 6's movement system, citing this as a potential reason for the game's appeal.

name: Listeria
summary: A deadly listeria outbreak linked to Boar's Head deli meats has claimed the lives of nine individuals, according to multiple news sources. Investigations have revealed the presence of bugs, mold, and mildew at a Boar's Head plant, which is believed to be the source of the contamination. The outbreak has affected individuals in 18 states, making it the largest listeria outbreak in the US since 2011. Public health officials urge consumers to check their refrigerators and discard any recalled deli meats to prevent further illness.
